# Verkada MCP Server

TypeScript MCP server wrapping the Verkada API. See `AGENTS.md` for full reference.

## Key facts

- **Entry:** `src/index.ts` — registers tools from `src/tools/{cameras,access,users,analytics}.ts`
- **API client:** `src/services/client.ts` — token exchange + `get/post/put/patch/delete`
- **HTTP credentials:** `AsyncLocalStorage` in `src/services/context.ts` → `getRequestClient()`
- **Tool naming:** `verkada_<action>_<resource>` (30 tools in repo)
- **Responses:** JSON as text; large lists truncated at 50k chars (`CHARACTER_LIMIT`)

## Auth (never store secrets in server for HTTP mode)

Headers: `x-verkada-api-key`, `x-verkada-org-id`, `x-verkada-region` (us|eu|au|oh)
Fallback env: `VERKADA_API_KEY`, `VERKADA_ORG_ID`, `VERKADA_REGION`

## Transports

- `TRANSPORT=stdio` (default) — local, env vars
- `TRANSPORT=http` — `POST /mcp`, credentials per request

## When editing

- Match existing tool patterns in `src/tools/`
- Run `npm run build` after TypeScript changes
- Cursor's `user-verkada` MCP may be a separate deployment with ~130 auto-generated tools
